title: Biden cancels visits to Australia and Papua New Guinea to deal with US debt crisis
description: President Joe Biden will cut a trip to Asia and Australia short to deal with the impending debt crisis in the US.

title: Child killed after hippo capsizes canoe - 23 other people feared dead
description: A one-year-old child has died and 23 other people are missing after a hippopotamus charged and capsized a canoe on a river in Malawi.

title: France's first lady calls out 'cowardice' of attack on her great-nephew
description: France's first lady has condemned the "cowardice" and "stupidity" of a physical attack on her great-nephew which took place on the sidelines of a protest against pension reforms.

title: Explosion linked to 'gender-based violence' kills two near playground in Spain
description: An explosion has killed two people in Spain, with authorities suspecting the blast was linked to "gender-based violence".

title: 'Share your secrets about Ukraine war,' CIA tells Russians
description: The CIA has urged Russians to share their secrets about the Ukraine war in a new video posted on social media.

title: COP28 climate summit offering multi-million pound sponsorship packages for exclusive access
description: COP28, the climate change conference taking place in Dubai this year, is asking brands for millions of pounds to sponsor the event, promising that they will "benefit from access and unrivalled networking opportunities with governments and global business leaders".

title: Before-and-after images show devastation of deadly Cyclone Mocha
description: Before-and-after images have revealed the devastation caused by deadly Cyclone Mocha.

title: Syrian president Assad invited to COP28 climate summit
description: Syria's president Bashar al Assad has been invited to attend this year's COP28 climate talks in Dubai.

title: The 'onion rings' of defences protecting Ukraine's cities from Russian missiles
description: Russian forces launched a huge barrage of 18 missiles at Kyiv on Tuesday. All of them were shot down, Ukraine says.

title: Nigerian chef cooks for 100 hours in bid for Guinness World Record
description: A chef has spent more than 100 hours cooking in a bid to achieve a new Guinness World Record.

title: Five jailed over multi-million euro jewellery heist
description: Five men have been convicted over the theft of 18th-century jewels worth more than 100m euros from a German museum

title: People in Japan are taking lessons to relearn how to smile
description: Smiling lessons are now available for people in Japan following three years of government recommendations that people wear masks.

title: Village People send 'cease and desist' letter to Trump over use of Macho Man song
description: Legendary US disco group the Village People have reportedly sent Donald Trump a legal letter after a video emerged of him dancing to one of their hit songs.

title: Man with metal baseball bat attacks employees at politician's office
description: A man with a metal baseball bat has attacked two employees at a politician's office in the US.
